The paper deals with the problem of cloud detection from RGB color images using deep learning techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of a deep pyramid network (DPN) and pre-trained parameter model at the encoder layer suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the segmentation and classification of pixels, which could place it under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of remote sensing data suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
